# Planning graph cache — derived from .planning/*.xml ledgers via
# `gad graph build` (auto-rebuilt on stale by `gad snapshot`/`gad startup`
# and by site/scripts/pack-site-release.cjs before producing the release
# zip). Tracking these produces noisy diffs on every task-status change
# and guaranteed parallel-agent merge conflicts that are never meaningful.
.planning/graph.json
.planning/graph.html

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Diff-noise reduction (2026-04-19, follow-up to graph cache cleanup).
# Every entry below is either (a) an append-only log written by every CLI
# call / hook, (b) per-agent local session state, or (c) deterministic
# build output regenerated by `npm run prebuild` (`site/scripts/
# build-site-data.mjs`). Tracking them caused 1,800+ commits / 60d of
# pure noise and guaranteed multi-agent merge conflicts. Source data
# (templates/, evals/, docs/, .planning/*.xml) stays tracked.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Tier 1: append-only logs + per-agent session state
#   trace events: bin/gad-trace-hook.cjs appends one JSONL line per CLI
#   call. Read by site/scripts/compute-self-eval.mjs at build time;
#   gracefully degrades to empty self-eval if missing.
.planning/.trace-events.jsonl
.planning/.trace-seq
#   gad-log: daily JSONL call log (.planning/.gad-log/YYYY-MM-DD.jsonl).
#   Same self-eval consumer; same graceful-empty fallback.
.planning/.gad-log/
#   sessions: per-agent local state created by `gad startup` /
#   `gad session new`. Each agent makes its own; never meant to share.
.planning/sessions/

# Tier 2: deterministic site build outputs (regenerated by
# `site/scripts/build-site-data.mjs`, run as `predev` / `prebuild` in
# site/package.json — so a fresh clone always produces these on first
# `npm run dev` or `npm run build`).
site/lib/*.generated.ts
site/lib/*.generated.json
site/data/*.json
site/public/llms.txt
site/public/llms-full.txt
site/public/api/docs.json
site/public/downloads/*.zip
site/public/downloads/planning/*.zip
